    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-03-07T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-03-07T14:00:00-05:00" n="610"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d610">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/6099: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-03-07T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 7, 1936—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>52. Shanghai’s 128, February 29, 5 p.m.,<note n="78" xml:id="d610fn78">Not found
                        in Department files.</note> transmits Commercial Attaché’s report to
                    Commerce “232, February 29. Supplement to Weekly Economic” which reads in part
                    as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Finance Minister appointed by National Government mandate to head the
                            commission for readjustment of domestic and foreign loans which now
                            consists of nine members of Ministerial rank from Government yuans
                            including also chairman of board of Bank of China.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Department desires to receive by naval radio such additional information as you
                    may have in regard to the commission under reference and would appreciate being
                    kept fully and currently advised of all developments of importance in regard
                    thereto.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
